# PII patterns to block from commits (template).
#
# Copy this file to `.githooks/pii-patterns` (gitignored) and add your own
# personal patterns. The actual `pii-patterns` file is per-contributor and is
# never committed, so each maintainer/contributor controls what their own
# pre-commit hook should reject.
#
# Format: one extended regex per line. Lines starting with `#` are comments.
# Add `pii-ok` as a comment on any line to suppress a match.
#
# A pre-commit hook script that reads this file is not bundled — wire one up
# yourself if you want pattern blocking on commit. Without a script, this file
# just documents the patterns you care about.

# Examples (uncomment and adapt — these are placeholders, not real values):

# Personal GitHub username (if different from your public identity)
# my-private-username

# Internal codenames or projects you don't want public
# internal-project-name

# Personal data that shouldn't appear in tests or code
# height.*=.*X\.YZ
# HEIGHT.*=.*X\.YZ

# Personal subdomains, deploy URLs, hostnames
# my-personal-host\.example\.com
